subsection.p:
Differentiate: dx=2s\,ds-dt, and dy=ds+2t\,dt. Then
dx\wedge dy \amp= (2s\,ds-dt)\wedge(ds+2t\,dt) \amp= 4st\,ds\wedge dt-dt\wedge ds \amp= 4st\,ds\wedge dt+ds\wedge dt \amp= (4st+1)\,ds\wedge dt.
Thus \boxed{\frac{\partial(x,y)}{\partial(s,t)}=4st+1.}

statement.p:
For the system in the previous problem, find
\frac{\partial u}{\partial x}\qquad\text{and}\qquad\frac{\partial v}{\partial x}
at (x,y)=(1,1).

subsubsection.p:
Compute the Jacobian matrix:
J_F(u,v)=\begin{pmatrix} x_u \amp x_v\\ y_u \amp y_v \end{pmatrix}.
Show that
\boxed{J_F(u,v)=\begin{pmatrix} 1 \amp 2v\\ 2u \amp 1 \end{pmatrix}}
and
\boxed{\det J_F(u,v)=1-4uv.}

